</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1954,2018]" lastBlockId="32.[151,1436,152,962]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,334,1954,1980]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity box="[550,683,1955,1981]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="15.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="14.0">14–16 mm</quantity>
. General overall forewing coloration is tan with darker brown shading along Cu vein, then angles slightly toward apex. There are two tiny black dots associated with vein Cu, one is at middle of discal cell below vein Cu and one at end of discal cell above vein Cu. Postmedial line consists of two tiny black dots, one on vein M2 and one on vein CuA2. Terminal line consists of a series of minute black dots. Hindwing is white variously and sometimes heavily suffused with gray. The outer margin is darker than the rest of the hindwing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,152,962]" box="[196,1039,301,327]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,369,301,327]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Flight period:</emphasis>
Late April to mid-October, two to three broods annually.
</paragraph>
