<taxonomicName box="[748,853,898,923]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Leucania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adjuta">L. adjuta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a grass feeder. Larvae obtained from eggs were reared on orchardgrass (
<taxonomicName box="[435,660,936,961]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dactylis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerata">
<emphasis box="[435,660,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Dactylis glomerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[707,805,936,962]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Godfrey, G. L." box="[828,998,936,962]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 265" refId="ref30677" refString="Godfrey, G. L. (1972) A review and reclassification of larvae of the subfamily Hadeninae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae) of American north of Mexico. U. S. Department of Agriculture Technical Bulletin, 1450, 1 - 265." type="journal article" year="1972">Godfrey 1972</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
